Deputy National Security Advisor Antony Blinken met with Secretary-General Dr. Ekmeleddin Ihsanoglu of the Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) to discuss the U.S.-OIC partnership and potential areas for further cooperation. They discussed the situation in Syria, including the ongoing fighting in Qusayr, and the need for a political solution. They also talked about Middle East peace, Burma, Afghanistan, and Iraq. Both parties agreed to expand cooperation on humanitarian crises, collaborate in the United Nations, and promote religious tolerance and freedom of expression worldwide. Deputy NSA Blinken expressed gratitude to Secretary-General Ihsanoglu for his leadership and promised to continue working closely with the OIC when the Secretary-General's successor takes office in 2014.